{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_01MVqgJ8MBApRgtsxUft3qys","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are confirmed met:\n\n- **`app-producer` is Ready** — `1/1 Running`, no restarts since the fix.\n- **`/app` vhost has `app-queue`, type `classic`, with messages** — currently 9 and growing (producer publishes continuously).\n- **Cluster remains healthy with 3 nodes** — `rabbitmq-0/1/2` all `Running`, all 3 listed as active cluster nodes.\n\nRoot cause: `app-user` had an empty `configure` permission regex on the `/app` vhost (write/read were `.*` but configure was blank), so the management API's `PUT /queues/%2Fapp/app-queue` call to declare the queue was refused with `not_authorised`, crash-looping the producer. Fix: `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` to grant configure rights, then restarted the producer pod. No CRDs/operators used, and no data was touched or lost — only a permission grant was applied."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":131,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1679,"cache_read_input_tokens":47221,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1679},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ff33e17b-6268-446a-9355-51eec111a061","uuid":"bcfeb159-f84b-4c11-a2b0-6141574ccfda","request_id":"req_011Ccat3rqijXm48tV9GW4jD"}
